{
    "header": "State supported python",
    "content": [
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "States support minimal python. You can use simple operations, some built in functions, one-line conditions and registered functions."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "State expressions in {} have access to all created states. You can not access outside variables (only through registered functions)."
        },
        {
            "type": "subheader",
            "text": "Allowed operations"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>+</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>-</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>/</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>*</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>%</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "subheader",
            "text": "Allowed built in functions"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>str()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>int()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>float()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>bool()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>abs()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>round()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>min()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>max()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>sum()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>len()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>range()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>enumerate()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>zip()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>sorted()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>reversed()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>all()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>any()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>repr()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>ord()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>chr()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "text-margin",
            "text": "<span class='val'>format()</span>"
        },
        {
            "type": "subheader",
            "text": "One-line conditions"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You can use all logical operators and you can also use <span class='param'>and</span>, <span class='param'>or</span> and <span class='param'>not</span> in one-line conditions."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Example below shows a simple one-line condition:"
        },
        {
            "type": "code",
            "lang": "python",
            "filename": "app.py",
            "header_color": "cornflowerblue",
            "code": [
                "<span class='str'>\"green\"</span> <span class='import'>if</span> score >= <span class='num'>10</span> <span class='import'>else</span> <span class='str'>\"red\"</span>"
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "subheader",
            "text": "Custom functions"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You can register a function the same way as for events. Registered functions can accept parameters that you can pass inside of state expression. Registered functions can return a value that can be used furthermore in the state expression's operations."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Example below shows a simple registered function that writes \"0\" before a number if the number is below 10:"
        },
        {
            "type": "code",
            "lang": "python",
            "filename": "app.py",
            "header_color": "cornflowerblue",
            "code": [
                "<span class='func'>@</span><span class='class'>DOM</span><span class='func'>.register<span><span class='paren'>()</span>",
                "<span class='keyw'>def</span> <span class='func'>adjust_number</span><span class='paren'>(</span><span class='param'>number</span>: <span class='class'>int</span><span class='paren'>)</span> -> <span class='class'>str</span>:",
                "\t<span class='import'>if</span> <span class='param'>number</span> >= <span class='num'>10</span>:",
                "\t\t<span class='import'>return</span> <span class='class'>str</span><span class='paren'>(</span><span class='param'>number</span><span class='paren'>)</span>",
                "",
                "\t<span class='import'>return</span> <span class='keyw'>f</span><span class='str'>\"0</span><span class='paren'>{</span><span class='param'>number</span><span class='paren'>}</span><span class='str'>\"</span>"
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "subheader",
            "text": "Lists"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You can access list values using <span class='param'>[index]</span>."
        },
        {
            "type": "subheader",
            "text": "Dictionaries"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You can access dict values using <span class='param'>dict[\"key\"]</span> or you can use <span class='param'>dict.get(\"key\", default_value)</span>."
        }
    ]
}